##add in whether 1 is churn or not churn##

#upload train dataset
train_data <- read.csv("~/Downloads/train_data.csv")
set.seed(123)

# View(train_data)
#These are the variables that need to be standardized: CreditScore, Age, Tenure, Balance, NumOfProducts, EstimatedSalary,Points.Earned.

train_data_std <- train_data
# View(train_data_std)


#numerical values only
library(dplyr)
## 
## Attaching package: 'dplyr'
## The following objects are masked from 'package:stats':
## 
##     filter, lag
## The following objects are masked from 'package:base':
## 
##     intersect, setdiff, setequal, union
train_data_num <- train_data %>% select_if(is.numeric)
correlation_matrix1 <- cor(train_data_num, use = "complete.obs")

#heatmap
library(ggcorrplot)
## Loading required package: ggplot2
ggcorrplot(cor(train_data_num), type = "lower", lab = TRUE, method = "circle", title = "Correlation Matrix Heatmap")

#Based on the heatmap, we decided to remove complain as a predictor variable since it has a 1:1 correlation with the target variable. 

#z score standardization
train_data_std$CreditScore <- (train_data$CreditScore - mean(train_data$CreditScore)/ sd(train_data$CreditScore))

train_data_std$Age <- (train_data$Age - mean(train_data$Age)/ sd(train_data$Age))

train_data_std$Tenure <- (train_data$Tenure - mean(train_data$Tenure)/ sd(train_data$Tenure))

train_data_std$Balance <- (train_data$Balance - mean(train_data$Balance)/ sd(train_data$Balance))

train_data_std$NumOfProducts <- (train_data$NumOfProducts - mean(train_data$NumOfProducts)/ sd(train_data$NumOfProducts))

train_data_std$EstimatedSalary <- (train_data$EstimatedSalary - mean(train_data$EstimatedSalary)/ sd(train_data$EstimatedSalary))

train_data_std$Point.Earned <- (train_data$Point.Earned - mean(train_data$Point.Earned)/ sd(train_data$Point.Earned))

#### Run forward, backward, stepwise model selection methods ####

null_model <- glm(Exited ~ 1, data = train_data_std, family="binomial") # no predictors
model <- glm(Exited ~ . -Complain, data = train_data_std, family="binomial") #all predictors except Complain


forward_model <- step(null_model, scope = list(lower = null_model, upper = model), direction = "forward")
